\c 7
\cl Numbers 7
\cd The offerings of the princes at the dedication of the tabernacle: God speaketh to Moses from the propitiatory.
\p
\v 1 And it came to pass in the day* that Moses had finished the tabernacle, and set it up, and had anointed and sanctified it with all its vessels, the altar likewise and all the vessels thereof,
\p
\v 2 The princes of Israel and the heads of the families, in every tribe, who were the rulers of them who had been numbered, offered*
\p
\v 3 Their gifts before the Lord, six waggons covered, and twelve oxen. Two princes offered one waggon, and each one an ox, and they offered them before the tabernacle.
\p
\v 4 And the Lord said to Moses:
\p
\v 5 Receive them from them to serve in the ministry of the tabernacle, and thou shalt deliver them to the Levites according to the order of their ministry.
\p
\v 6 Moses therefore receiving the waggons and the oxen, delivered them to the Levites.
\p
\v 7 Two waggons and four oxen he gave to the sons of Gerson, according to their necessity.
\p
\v 8 The other four waggons, and eight oxen, he gave to the sons of Merari, according to their offices and service, under the hand of Ithamar, the son of Aaron, the priest.
\p
\v 9 But to the sons of Caath he gave no waggons or oxen: because they serve in the sanctuary, and carry their burdens upon their own shoulders.
\p
\v 10 And the princes offered for the dedication of the altar, on the day when it was anointed, their oblation before the altar.
\p
\v 11 And the Lord said to Moses: Let each of the princes, one day after another, offer their gifts for the dedication of the altar.
\p
\v 12 The first day Nahasson, the son of Aminadab, of the tribe of Juda, offered his offering:
\p
\v 13 And his offering was a silver dish, weighing one hundred and thirty sicles, a silver bowl of seventy sicles, according to the weight of the sanctuary, both full of flour tempered with oil, for a sacrifice:
\p
\v 14 A little mortar, of ten sicles of gold, full of incense:
\p
\v 15 An ox of the herd, and a ram, and a lamb of a year old for a holocaust:
\p
\v 16 And a buck-goat for sin:
\p
\v 17 And for the sacrifice of peace-offerings, two oxen, five rams, five he-goats, five lambs of a year old. This was the offering of Nahasson, the son of Aminadab.
\p
\v 18 The second day Nathanael, the son of Suar, prince of the tribe of Issachar, made his offering:
\p
\v 19 A silver dish, weighing one hundred and thirty sicles, a silver bowl of seventy sicles, according to the weight of the sanctuary, both full of flour tempered with oil, for a sacrifice:
\p
\v 20 A little mortar of gold, weighing ten sicles, full of incense:
\p
\v 21 An ox of the herd, and a ram, and a lamb of a year old for a holocaust:
\p
\v 22 And a buck-goat for sin:
\p
\v 23 And for the sacrifice of peace-offerings, two oxen, five rams, five buck-goats, five lambs of a year old. This was the offering of Nathanael, the son of Suar.
\p
\v 24 The third day the prince of the sons of Zabulon, Eliab, the son of Helon,
\p
\v 25 Offered a silver dish, weighing one hundred and thirty sicles, a silver bowl of seventy sicles, by the weight of the sanctuary, both full of flour tempered with oil, for a sacrifice:
\p
\v 26 A little mortar of gold, weighing ten sicles, full of incense:
\p
\v 27 An ox of the herd, and a ram, and a lamb of a year old for a holocaust:
\p
\v 28 And a buck-goat for sin:
\p
\v 29 And for the sacrifice of peace-offerings, two oxen, five rams, five buck-goats, five lambs of a year old. This is the oblation of Eliab, the son of Helon.
\p
\v 30 The fourth day the prince of the sons of Ruben, Elisur, the son of Sedeur,
\p
\v 31 Offered a silver dish, weighing one hundred and thirty sicles, a silver bowl of seventy sicles, according to the weight of the sanctuary, both full of flour tempered with oil, for a sacrifice:
\p
\v 32 A little mortar of gold, weighing ten sicles, full of incense:
\p
\v 33 An ox of the herd, and a ram, and a lamb of a year old for a holocaust:
\p
\v 34 And a buck-goat for sin:
\p
\v 35 And for victims of peace-offerings, two oxen, five rams, five buck-goats, five lambs of a year old. This was the offering of Elisur, the son of Sedeur.
\p
\v 36 The fifth day the prince of the sons of Simeon, Salamiel, the son of Surisaddai,
\p
\v 37 Offered a silver dish, weighing one hundred and thirty sicles, a silver bowl of seventy sicles, after the weight of the sanctuary, both full of flour tempered with oil, for a sacrifice:
\p
\v 38 A little mortar of gold, weighing ten sicles, full of incense:
\p
\v 39 An ox of the herd, and a ram, and a lamb of a year old for a holocaust:
\p
\v 40 And a buck-goat for sin:
\p
\v 41 And for sacrifices of peace-offerings, two oxen, five rams, five buck-goats, five lambs of a year old. This was the offering of Salamiel, the son of Surisaddai.
\p
\v 42 The sixth day the prince of the sons of Gad, Eliasaph, the son of Duel,
\p
\v 43 Offered a silver dish, weighing a hundred and thirty sicles, a silver bowl of seventy sicles, by the weight of the sanctuary, both full of flour tempered with oil, for a sacrifice:
\p
\v 44 A little mortar of gold, weighing ten sicles, full of incense:
\p
\v 45 An ox of the herd, and a ram, and a lamb of a year old for a holocaust:
\p
\v 46 And a buck-goat for sin:
\p
\v 47 And for sacrifices of peace-offerings, two oxen, five rams, five buck-goats, five lambs of a year old. This was the offering of Eliasaph, the son of Duel.
\p
\v 48 The seventh day the prince of the sons of Ephraim, Elisama, the son Ammiud,
\p
\v 49 Offered a silver dish, weighing a hundred and thirty sicles, a silver bowl of seventy sicles, according to the weight of the sanctuary, both full of flour tempered with oil, for a sacrifice:
\p
\v 50 A little mortar of gold, weighing ten sicles, full of incense :
\p
