\p
\v 62 A little mortar of gold, weighing ten sicles, full of incense:
\p
\v 63 An ox of the herd, and a ram, and a lamb of a year old for a holocaust:
\p
\v 64 And a buck-goat for sin:
\p
\v 65 And for sacrifices of peace-offerings, two oxen, five rams, five buck-goats, five lambs of a year old. This was the offering of Abidan, the son of Gedeon.
\p
\v 66 The tenth day the prince of the sons of Dan, Ahiezer, the son of Ammisaddai,
\p
\v 67 Offered a silver dish, weighing a hundred and thirty sicles, a silver bowl of seventy sicles, according to the weight of the sanctuary, both full of flour tempered with oil, for a sacrifice:
\p
