\c 29
\cl Numbers 29
\cd Sacrifices for the festivals of the seventh month.
\p
\v 1 The first day also of the seventh month shall be venerable and holy unto you: you shall do no servile work therein, because it is the day of the sounding and of trumpets.
\p
\v 2 And you shall offer a holocaust for a most sweet odour to the Lord, one calf of the herd, one ram, and seven lambs of a year old, without blemish:
\p
\v 3 And for their sacrifices, three tenths of flour tempered with oil to every calf, two tenths to a ram,
\p
\v 4 One tenth to a lamb, which in all are seven lambs:
\p
\v 5 And a buck-goat for sin, which is offered for the expiation of the people,
\p
\v 6 Besides the holocaust of the first day of the month, with the sacrifices thereof, and the perpetual holocaust with the accustomed libations. With the same ceremonies you shall offer a burnt-sacrifice for a most sweet odour to the Lord.
\p
\v 7 *The tenth day also of this seventh month shall be holy and venerable unto you, and you shall afflict your souls: you shall do no servile work therein.
\p
\v 8 And you shall offer a holocaust to the Lord for a most sweet odour, one calf of the herd, one ram, and seven lambs of a year old, without blemish:
\p
\v 9 And for their sacrifices, three tenths of flour tempered with oil to every calf, two tenths to a ram,
\p
\v 10 The tenth of a tenth to every lamb, which are in all seven lambs:
\p
\v 11 And a buck-goat for sin, besides the things that are wont to be offered for sin, for expiation, and for the perpetual holocaust, with their sacrifice and libations.
\p
\v 12 And on the fifteenth day of the seventh month, which shall be unto you holy and venerable, you shall do no servile work, but shall celebrate a solemnity to the Lord seven days.
\p
\v 13 And you shall offer a holocaust for a most sweet odour to the Lord, thirteen calves of the herd, two rams, and fourteen lambs of a year old, without blemish:
\p
\v 14 And for their libations, three tenths of flour tempered with oil to every calf, being in all thirteen calves: and two tenths to each ram, being two rams,
\p
\v 15 And the tenth of a tenth to every lamb, being in all fourteen lambs:
\p
\v 16 And a buck-goat for sin, besides the perpetual holocaust, and the sacrifice, and the libation thereof.
\p
\v 17 On the second day you shall offer twelve calves of the herd, two rams, and fourteen lambs of a year old, without blemish:
\p
\v 18 And the sacrifices and the libations for every one, for the calves and for the rams, and for the lambs you shall duly celebrate:
\p
\v 19 And a buck-goat for a sin-offering, besides the perpetual holocaust, and the sacrifice and the libation thereof.
\p
\v 20 The third day you shall offer eleven calves, two rams, and fourteen lambs of a year old, without blemish:
\p
\v 21 And the sacrifices and the libations of every one for the calves and for the rams, and for the lambs you shall offer according to the rite:
\p
\v 22 And a buck-goat for sin, besides the perpetual holocaust, and the sacrifice, and the libation thereof.
\p
\v 23 The fourth day you shall offer ten calves, two rams, and fourteen lambs of a year old, without blemish:
\p
\v 24 And the sacrifices and the libations of every one for the calves and for the rams, and for the lambs you shall celebrate in right manner:
\p
\v 25 And a buck-goat for sin, besides the perpetual holocaust, and the sacrifice and the libation thereof.
\p
\v 26 The fifth day you shall offer nine calves, two rams, and fourteen lambs of a year old, without blemish:
\p
\v 27 And the sacrifices and the libations of every one for the calves and for the rams, and for the lambs, you shall celebrate according to the rite:
\p
\v 28 And a buck-goat for sin, besides the perpetual holocaust, and the sacrifice and the libation thereof.
\p
\v 29 The sixth day you shall offer eight calves, two rams, and fourteen lambs of a year old, without blemish:
\p
\v 30 And the sacrifices and the libations of every one for the calves and for the rams, and for the lambs, you shall celebrate according to the rite:
\p
\v 31 And a buck-goat for sin, besides the perpetual holocaust, and the sacrifice thereof and the libation.
\p
\v 32 The seventh day you shall offer seven calves, and two rams, and fourteen lambs of a year old, without blemish.
\p
\v 33 And the sacrifices and the libations of every one for the calves and for the rams, and for the lambs, you shall celebrate according to the rite:
\p
\v 34 And a buck-goat for sin, besides the perpetual holocaust, and the sacrifice and the libation thereof.
\p
\v 35 On the eighth day, which is most solemn, you shall do no servile work:
\p
\v 36 But you shall offer a holocaust for a most sweet odour to the Lord, one calf, one ram, and seven lambs of a year old, without blemish:
\p
\v 37 And the sacrifices and the libations of every one for the calves and for the rams, and for the lambs, you shall celebrate according to the rite:
\p
\v 38 And a buck-goat for sin, besides the perpetual holocaust, and the sacrifice and the libation thereof.
\p
\v 39 These things shall you offer to the Lord in your solemnities: besides your vows and voluntary oblations for holocaust, for sacrifice, for libation, and for victims of peace-offerings.
\x + \xo 29:7\xt Leviticus 16:29.; Leviticus 23:27.\x*
\f + \fr 29:1\ft The first. This day was doubly solemn, as being the first day of the month, consequently entitled to all the sacrifices enjoined for it; and also a holiday, for which other victims are requisite, besides the perpetual holocausts, (Numbers 29:2-6.; Numbers 28:11.) (Haydock)\f*
\f + \fr 29:7\ft Tenth. The feast of expiation, on which see (Leviticus 16:29.; and 23:24.) where we have also explained what relates to the feast of tabernacles, ver. 34.\f*
\f + \fr 29:12\ft Seven days, not refraining indeed all that time from servile work, but remaining under tents, and daily performing what is required, ver. 13., etc.\f*
\f + \fr 29:35\ft Eighth day, which was more solemn than the preceding ones, but less so than the first. The victims are every day diminished. (Calmet) --- This day, in the Hebrew calendar, is called the feast of retention, (atsroth) as they staid near the tabernacle. (Du Hamel)\f*
\f + \fr 29:39\ft Vows. The general regulations did not hinder any private ones from being fulfilled. (Calmet) --- Sacrifice. Mincha, or offering of flour, etc. (Haydock)\f*
